# Component Rules

- Separate clearly:
  - `Page`: route-level composition
  - `Container`: business logic + state wiring
  - `UI Component (dumb)`: presentation only
- Complex component logic must be moved to custom hooks (`useSomething.ts`).
- Components should focus on rendering UI; side effects and orchestration belong in hooks/containers.
- Keep component files under 200 lines. Split when the component becomes large or hard to scan.
- Avoid deeply nested logic; use early return to keep control flow flat.
- Use `React.memo`, `useMemo`, `useCallback` only for proven re-render/perf issues.
- Apply code splitting for pages or heavy modules:

```tsx
const CampaignPage = lazy(() => import('./CampaignPage'));
```
